 07  2015 The Virginia Military Institute invites applications for the position of Media Instructional Technologist at Preston Library  Founded in 1839  VMI is an undergraduate institution which enrolls approximately 1 700 full time cadets and is ranked consistently among the nation s top liberal arts colleges  Reporting to the Head of Media Services  the position assists in supporting media technologies and instruction for students and faculty  Essential responsibilities include    Ability to work with students and faculty individually or in groups    Provide professional leadership and technical skills in applications of technology to enhance instruction and improve student learning    Provide technology training and consultation to assist faculty in their teaching and research    Contribute to educational success through the application of advanced technology skills  understanding instructional needs  and application of software and hardware solutions    Supervise  train  and schedule student assistants to ensure knowledgeable  customer oriented service  Qualifications  Master s degree in instructional design  instructional technology  education or a related field  At least three years of experience working at an institute of higher education  expertise with a learning management system  LMS  experience working with faculty one on one or in a group  experience designing and leading training workshops  expertise in the creation of instructional content using digital tools  proven ability to work well in a team environment  demonstrated creativity and problem solving skills  excellent oral and written communication skills  The successful candidate will be a creative thinker and energetic collaborator with a strong interest in helping faculty transform their teaching and assist them in technology based learning solutions to enhance student learning  The ability to be professionally engaged in learning new technologies is essential  Candidates must apply on line at  